trans-unit.source: This topic discusses the entities and complex types that are exposed by the Graph API.
trans-unit.target: 本主题讨论的实体和关系图 API 公开的复杂类型。

trans-unit.source: The Graph API is an OData 3.0 compliant REST API that provides programmatic access to directory objects in Azure Active Directory, such as users, groups, organizational contacts, and applications.
trans-unit.target: Graph API 是一个 OData 3.0 符合 REST API，它提供对在 Azure Active Directory，如用户、 组、 组织联系人和应用程序的目录对象的编程访问。

trans-unit.source: [!IMPORTANT] Azure AD Graph API functionality is also available through [Microsoft Graph](https://graph.microsoft.io/), a unified API that also includes APIs from other Microsoft services like Outlook, OneDrive, OneNote, Planner, and Office Graph, all accessed through a single endpoint with a single access token.
trans-unit.target: [!IMPORTANT] 它也可通过 azure AD Graph API 功能 [Microsoft Graph](https://graph.microsoft.io/), ，如 Outlook、 OneDrive、 OneNote、 计划者和 Office 关系图中，通过使用单个访问令牌的单个终结点访问所有服务的一个统一的 API，它还包括来自其他 Microsoft Api。

trans-unit.source: Any application that outsources authentication to Azure AD must be registered in a directory.
trans-unit.target: 将身份验证外包给 Azure AD 的任何应用程序都必须在目录中进行注册。

trans-unit.source: This involves telling Azure AD about your application, including the URL where it's located, the URL to send replies after authentication, the URI to identify your application, and more.
trans-unit.target: 这涉及告诉 Azure AD 关于你的应用程序，包括它具有处的位置，要将回复发送身份验证后，要确定您的应用程序及更多内容的 URI 的 URL 的 URL。

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Basics of Registering an Application in Azure AD](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-authentication-scenarios/#basics-of-registering-an-application-in-azure-ad).

trans-unit.source: Organizational contacts represent users that are not in your company directory.
trans-unit.target: 组织联系人代表用户不在你公司的目录中。

trans-unit.source: They are mail-enabled entities and typically represent individuals who are external to your company or organization.
trans-unit.target: 它们是已启用邮件的实体，通常表示对贵公司或组织外部的人员。

trans-unit.source: Organizational contacts cannot be authenticated using Azure AD, nor can they be assigned licenses.
trans-unit.target: 无法使用 Azure AD 身份验证组织的联系人，也可以将它们分配许可证。

trans-unit.source: Organizational contacts can be created in your tenant through syncing with an on-premises directory using Azure AD Connect, or they can be created through one of the Exchange Online management portals or the Exchange Online PowerShell cmdlets.
trans-unit.target: 可以在通过与使用 Azure AD Connect，一个在本地目录同步你的租户中创建组织的联系人或要通过 Exchange Online 的管理门户或 Exchange Online PowerShell cmdlet 之一创建它们。

trans-unit.source: For more information about Azure AD Connect, see [Integrating your on-premises identities with Azure Active Directory](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-aadconnect/).
trans-unit.target: 有关 Azure AD Connect 的详细信息，请参阅 [与 Azure Active Directory 集成本地标识](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-aadconnect/)。

trans-unit.source: For more information about Exchange Online management tools, see [Exchange Online Setup and Administration](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/exchange-online-administration-and-management.aspx#BKMK_ExchangeAdministrationCenter).
trans-unit.target: 有关 Exchange Online 管理工具的详细信息，请参阅 [Exchange Online 设置和管理](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/exchange-online-administration-and-management.aspx#BKMK_ExchangeAdministrationCenter)。
